   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Medical Credit Fund</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The private healthcare sector in Africa delivers more than half of the continent&#x2019;s healthcare services but is chronically underfunded, with access to finance being a major barrier. The Medical Credit Fund (MCF) was established to increase access to better healthcare services in sub-Saharan Africa for low-income patients by providing flexible local currency debt finance through risk-sharing partnerships with local financial institutions. The loans are typically made to small and medium sized healthcare providers for renovations, medical equipment and working capital.</narrative>
  </description>
